    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Consul General at Rangoon (
                        Packer
                    ) to the Secretary of
                            State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1947v06</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d22</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">22</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1947-03-24T23:30:00-05:00" notAfter="1947-03-24T23:30:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-03-24T23:30:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-03-24T23:30:00-05:00" n="22" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d22">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">845C.00/3–2547: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Rangoon</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Packer</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rangoon</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-03-25T11:00:00+06:30">March 25, 1947—11 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>234. Supreme Council United Hill Peoples now in session at Tounggyi has just
                    decided Hill Peoples will participate in work of Constituent Assembly. Manner of
                    participation still to be worked out.<note n="50" xml:id="d22fn50">Telegram 335,
                        April 28, from Rangoon, reported the signing on April 24 at Maymyo of the
                        “unanimous report Frontier Areas Inquiry Committee on best method
                        associating frontier areas peoples with framing Burma’s new constitution”.
                        (845C.9111 RR/4–2847) This Committee was headed by Lt. Col. D. R.
                        Rees-Williams, member of the British House of Commons; for text of report,
                        see British Cmd. 7138.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Repeated London as 51.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Packer</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
